<br>
I would have to say I think it's a key component of being a hero, and I think Joseph Campbell has my back on this one. Think of the great heroes of legend and myth.<br>
<br>
Hercules is a hero because he was redeeming himself for something pretty horrible (drunkenly killing his family), not because he could turn rivers around to clean horse poop away.<br>
<br>
Spider-Man is a hero because the temptation is always there to only worry about himself, but he knows from his own life that selfishness like that will kill innocent people, such as his own uncle.<br>
<br>
Bilbo Baggins was a hero because, although he really wanted just his creature comforts and to maybe bring home a little coin, he risked his life -- needlessly and repeatedly -- to save others, simply because he saw something that needed doing and did it, even though it could have meant his own life.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> Li Mu Bai didn't grow all that much either... He and Shu Lien were primarily static characters until the very end, and even then their expressions of love for each other were really just final realizations of truths they had both known for a long time.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
But, in repressed Ang Lee world, that IS a big accomplishment. They'd recognized their two biggest flaws and, in that moment they held hands, overcome them. Their story was over, and they had won. The death afterwards wasn't really that important in the grand scheme of things.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> Luke certianly did grow, the calm and competent Jedi that faught Jabba and stood before the Emperor was certianly not the same crybaby kid that Han had to deal with in the original Episode.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
He was still a giant crybaby at the end. He just had more scars and abilities. He hadn't overcome any personal obstacles or grown as a person one bit. Compare that to Han Solo, who tossed away his entire worldview when he realized he needed to do the right thing.<br>
<br>
Luke Skywalker is the Percival of Star Wars. He might be the one starring in the Brothers Hildebrandt poster and be the big name guy, but he's still a twit and not very heroic, even if he does win the day. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uvashanti.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Vashanti</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://home.tampabay.rr.com/eqsite/bullet3.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Sorcerer<br>Iron Chef - EverQuest</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(3/2/02 11:37:06 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm40.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=5.topic&index=21>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://web.tampabay.rr.com/eqsite/Vashanti/Vash_Luclin_Face.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Vote for your hero!</span><hr size=1> ...<br>
